"1260","about 1240":"oko 1240.","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"cs":{"about 1240–about 1260":"okolo 1240–okolo 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Zesnulá","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"okolo 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"okolo 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1240–about 1260":"omkring 1240–omkring 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Afdød","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"omkring 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"omkring 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"nl":{"about 1240–about 1260":"circa 1240–circa 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Overleden","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"circa 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"circa 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{"about 1240–about 1260":"about 1240–about 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Deceased","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"about 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"about 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tucker","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name from Middle English <i>tuker(e)</i>, <i>toker(e)</i> ‘tucker, fuller’, a derivative of <i>tuken</i> ‘to torment, beat’ (Old English <i>tūcian</i>), for someone who fulled and finished cloth. This name for the occupation was characteristic of the West Country. Compare   Fuller   and   Walker   and see also   Tuckerman  .","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Tuachair</b> ‘descendant of <i>Tuachar</i>’, a personal name composed of the elements <i>tuath</i> ‘people’ + <i>car</i> ‘dear, beloved’.","Americanized form of Jewish <b>Tocker</b> or <b>Toker</b> (see   Tokarz  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Tooker","meanings":["English (Devon) and Irish: variant of   Tucker  ."]},{"name":"Tuckerman","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>tuker(e)</i>, <i>toker(e)</i> ‘tucker, fuller’ (see   Tucker   1) + <i>-man</i>, either for a tucker, or for his servant or assistant."]},{"name":"Fuller","meanings":["English: occupational name for a dresser of cloth, from Middle English <i>fuller</i> ‘fuller of cloth’ (partly from Old English <i>fullere</i>, partly from Old French <i>fouleor</i>, <i>foleur</i>, Latin <i>fullo</i>). Raw cloth had to be fulled, i.e. scoured, cleansed, and thickened by beating or trampling it in water, a process also known as <i>walking</i> or <i>tucking</i>, hence the surnames   Walker   and   Tucker   alongside <i>Fuller</i>. These three terms and surnames are characteristic of different parts of England. In general, in Middle English, <i>Fuller</i> is southern and eastern, while <i>Walker</i> belongs to the west and north and <i>Tucker</i> is southwestern. Compare   Fullen  .","English: variant of   Fullard   with loss of <i>-d</i>.","German (<b>Füller</b>): occupational name for a person whose work involved filling, such as a dauber, or a nickname for a gourmand or glutton. Compare   Filler  ."]},{"name":"Swinger","meanings":["English: occupational name, perhaps for a fuller, who finished cloth by beating it and stretching it on tenters. Middle English swyngere is not independently recorded but it appears to be an agent derivative of Middle English <i>swingen</i> ‘to beat, strike, punish, afflict (something)’. Compare the synonymous   Tucker  , an agent derivative of Middle English <i>tuken</i> ‘to torment, beat’. The earliest bearers of the name <i>Swinger</i> were wealthy townsmen.","In some instances probably an Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Schwinger  , or German <b>Zwinger</b>, a nickname from Middle High German <i>zwinger</i> ‘oppressor’."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry Tucker was born about 1240, in Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom as the son of James Tucker. He had at least 1 son with Ellen Stockes. He died about 1260, at the age of 22."},"et":{"about 1240–about 1260":"umbes 1240–umbes 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"umbes 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1240–about 1260":"noin 1240–noin 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"noin 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"noin 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1240–about 1260":"environ 1240–environ 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"environ 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"environ 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Henry Tucker est né environ 1240, à Throwleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de James Tucker. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ellen Stockes. Il est décédé environ 1260, à l’âge de 22 ans."},"de":{"about 1240–about 1260":"um 1240–um 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Verstorben","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"um 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"um 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","lifeSummary":"Henry Tucker wurde um 1240 in Throwleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom, als Sohn von James Tucker geboren. Er hatte mit Ellen Stockes mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb um 1260 im Alter von 22 Jahren."},"ht":{"about 1240–about 1260":"about 1240–about 1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–Desede","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"about 1260","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"about 1240","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Angletè, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"hu":{"about 1240–about 1260":"1240 körül–1260 körül","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1240–Female":"1240–elhunyt","1273–1320":"1273–1320","1210–1260":"1210–1260","about 1260":"1260 körül","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1260":"1260","about 1240":"1240 körül","Throwleigh, Devon, England":"Throwleigh, Devon, Anglia, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"id":{"about 1240–about 1260":"se